canRunInNewSession() → allows execution in a new session.

description() → gives the job a name.

canGoBatchJournal() → allows logging.

runsImpersonated() → runs under impersonation (security context).

canGoBatch() → confirms it can run as a batch process.
  --------------------------------------------
public static void main (Args _args)
{
    DonationListJob donationListJob = DonationListJob::construct();
    
    if (donationListJob.prompt())
    {
        donationListJob.runOperation();
    }
}
Entry point if run directly.

Calls prompt() → shows the dialog.

If the user confirms, runOperation() executes.
